Author: Alright#0419
Content:
```
#!/usr/bin/env python3

import stakerlib
from slickrpc import Proxy
from datetime import datetime
rpc = stakerlib.def_credentials('LABS')

listunspent = rpc.listunspent()

latest = 0
for utxo in listunspent:
    if utxo['rawconfirmations'] > latest and utxo['generated'] == True:
        latest = utxo['rawconfirmations']
        latest_utxo = utxo

getraw = rpc.getrawtransaction(utxo['txid'],2)
days = (int(datetime.now().timestamp()) - getraw['blocktime'])/86400
print('It is ' + str(datetime.utcfromtimestamp(datetime.now().timestamp())) + ' UTC and you haven\'t mined a block in ' + str(days) + 'DAYS bitch!\n')
print(latest_utxo)
```

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: @kmdkrazy too much bro... what are your system specs??? just because an Intel iX core from the 4th gen and up can compete with others for PoS hashing... doesnt mean your whole CPU RAM and the drive used is going to work well for ~15K utxos.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: This is where my statements earlier about hardware really matter

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: more utxos means more reads from disk means more i/o needed to evaluate thousands of utxos in the time the segid is valid

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: There is most definitely a mathematical ceiling that could be calculated based on all those factors.

Author: daemonfox#6136
Content: Just like alright pointed out utxos that havent staked after 30 days are wasting potential... a wallet on a subpar disk trying to hash through a thousands lines on utxos in time before the segid shift may be more than your setup is prepared to handle... especially with your scripts constantly watching the wallet and log files.
